@startuml
title Ticket Management System - Sequence Diagram

actor Requester
participant "Ticket Portal" as Portal
participant "Ticket Service" as Ticket
participant "SLA Engine" as SLA
participant "Notification Service" as Notify
participant "Support Agent" as Agent
participant "Specialist Team" as Specialist
participant "Knowledge Base" as KB

Requester -> Portal: Create ticket
Portal -> Ticket: Submit ticket data
Ticket -> Ticket: Validate request
Ticket -> SLA: Calculate priority and due date
SLA --> Ticket: SLA target
Ticket -> Notify: Send ticket created message
Notify --> Requester: Ticket ID and status

Ticket -> Agent: Assign ticket
Agent -> Ticket: Review ticket details
Agent -> KB: Search known solution
KB --> Agent: Suggested article or workaround

alt First level can resolve
  Agent -> Ticket: Add resolution note
  Ticket -> Notify: Ask requester to confirm
  Notify --> Requester: Resolution confirmation request
else Escalation required
  Agent -> Specialist: Escalate ticket
  Specialist -> Ticket: Investigate and update root cause
  Specialist -> Ticket: Add final resolution
  Ticket -> Notify: Ask requester to confirm
end

alt Requester accepts
  Requester -> Portal: Confirm resolved
  Portal -> Ticket: Close ticket
  Ticket -> Notify: Send closure and survey
else Requester rejects
  Requester -> Portal: Reopen ticket
  Portal -> Ticket: Change status to Reopened
  Ticket -> Agent: Notify owner
end

@enduml
